title Claim-Source Mapping Architecture\nMulti-Agent Synthesis with Citation Preservation

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
'  Participants
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
actor       "User"                    as U       #E3F2FD
participant "Orchestrator"            as O       #E8EAF6
participant "Web Search\nAgent"       as WSA     #E0F7FA
participant "Document\nAnalysis Agent" as DAA    #F3E5F5
participant "Synthesis Agent"         as SA      #FFF3E0
database    "Source Registry"         as SR      #E8F5E9

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
'  1. Query Dispatch
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
== 1 · Query Dispatch ==

U  ->  O  : submit query
O  ->  WSA : dispatch(search_task)
O  ->  DAA : dispatch(document_task)

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
'  2. Subagent: Web Search
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
== 2 · Subagents Produce Structured ClaimSourceMappings ==

group Web Search Agent
  WSA -> WSA : fetch & rank web results
  WSA -> WSA : extract claims from content
  WSA ->  SR : register(source_id → {url, title, snippets[]})

  note right of WSA
    ClaimSourceMapping — WSA Output
    ─────────────────────────────────────
    {
      "claims": [
        {
          "claim_id"  : "c1",
          "text"      : "X increases Y by 30%",
          "citations" : [
            { "source_id": "s1", "snippet_idx": 2 },
            { "source_id": "s2", "snippet_idx": 0 }
          ]
        },
        {
          "claim_id"  : "c2",
          "text"      : "Adoption rate doubled in 2024",
          "citations" : [
            { "source_id": "s2", "snippet_idx": 3 }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "sources": {
        "s1": { "url": "https://...", "snippets": ["...", "...", "

"] },
        "s2": { "url": "https://...", "snippets": ["

", "...", "...", "

"] }
      }
    }
    ─────────────────────────────────────
    Every claim carries at least one
    citationId:snippetIndex pair.
  end note

  WSA --> O : ClaimSourceMapping_WSA
end

group Document Analysis Agent
  DAA -> DAA : parse & chunk documents
  DAA -> DAA : attribute claims to passages
  DAA ->  SR : register(source_id → {doc_id, page, snippets[]})

  note right of DAA
    ClaimSourceMapping — DAA Output
    ─────────────────────────────────────
    {
      "claims": [
        {
          "claim_id"  : "c3",
          "text"      : "Studies confirm the Z pattern",
          "citations" : [
            { "source_id": "s3", "snippet_idx": 1 }
          ]
        },
        {
          "claim_id"  : "c4",
          "text"      : "Failure rate drops below 5%",
          "citations" : [
            { "source_id": "s4", "snippet_idx": 0 },
            { "source_id": "s4", "snippet_idx": 5 }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "sources": {
        "s3": { "doc_id": "rpt-2024-Q3", "page": 4,  "snippets": ["...", "

"] },
        "s4": { "doc_id": "whitepaper-v2", "page": 11, "snippets": ["

", ..., "

"] }
      }
    }
    ─────────────────────────────────────
    Document page + snippet index are
    preserved for deep-link citations.
  end note

  DAA --> O : ClaimSourceMapping_DAA
end

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
'  3. Synthesis Agent — Merge & Preserve
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
== 3 · Synthesis Agent Merges & Preserves Mappings ==

O  ->  SA : forward([ClaimSourceMapping_WSA, ClaimSourceMapping_DAA])

SA -> SA : merge source registries\n(deduplicate, re-key on conflict)

note over SA
  Merge Algorithm
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  Step 1 — Build unified SourceRegistry
           Merge s1…s4; on duplicate URL/doc_id,
           keep single canonical entry, union snippets[].

  Step 2 — Preserve every claim → [source:snippet] edge
           NEVER drop a citation during combination.
           Union citations when two agents cite the same claim.

  Step 3 — Conflict resolution
           If two agents produce contradicting claims,
           surface BOTH with their respective citations;
           do not silently discard either.

  Step 4 — Validate coverage
           claims with citations[]  = []  → flag UNSUPPORTED
           UNSUPPORTED claims must NOT appear in final report
           without explicit uncertainty markers.

  Step 5 — Emit inline tags Each sentence referencing claim cN becomes: "…finding…cN:sX:snippetIdx."
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────
end note

SA -> SA : generate narrative prose\nwith inline cN:sX:idx
SA -> SA : produce MergedClaimSourceMap\n(full provenance graph)

SA --> O : FinalReport + MergedClaimSourceMap

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
'  4. Output Validation Gate
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
== 4 · Orchestrator Validates Citation Coverage ==

O -> O : parse FinalReport\ncheck every claim has ≥1 citation

alt ✅ All claims cited
  O --> U : Final Report\n(full source attribution preserved)
else ⚠️ UNSUPPORTED claims detected
  O --> SA : re-request with\nflagged claim_ids list
  SA --> O  : patched FinalReport
  O --> U  : Final Report (patched)
end

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
'  5. Data Structure Legend
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
== 5 · ClaimSourceMapping Schema (Canonical Contract) ==

note over O, SR
  ClaimSourceMapping — Canonical Contract (all subagents MUST conform)
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ClaimSourceMapping {
    claims  : Claim[]          // ordered list of extracted claims
    sources : Map<SourceID, Source>  // complete source registry
  }

  Claim {
    claim_id   : string        // unique within agent scope; prefixed on merge
    text       : string        // verbatim or paraphrased claim text
    confidence : float         // 0.0–1.0 agent confidence score
    citations  : Citation[]    // REQUIRED; must be non-empty
  }

  Citation {
    source_id   : SourceID     // key into sources map
    snippet_idx : int          // index into source.snippets[]
  }

  Source {
    source_id : SourceID
    type      : "web" | "document" | "database"
    url?      : string         // for web sources
    doc_id?   : string         // for document sources
    page?     : int            // optional page reference
    snippets  : string[]       // ordered array of extracted passages
  }
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Synthesis agent MUST output the same schema with merged sources.
  Inline citation format: claim_id:source_id:snippet_idx
end note

@enduml